WEBVTT

00:02.339 --> 00:04.375
Turk, I totally ruined Izzy's life.

00:04.513 --> 00:05.944
Already? It's only 8:30.

00:06.191 --> 00:09.244
I totally forgot there was a parent's
meeting for her play group this morning.

00:09.384 --> 00:11.818
Now she's gonna get kicked out.
She won't have any friends.

00:11.902 --> 00:15.121
She's gonna drop out of high school.
She's gonna start dating some gangbanger,

00:15.328 --> 00:18.575
who you're gonna harass over and over and
over again, to get his life together,

00:18.685 --> 00:21.670
until he snaps and shoots you in
the face... Oh my God!

00:21.725 --> 00:25.481
Whoa! You're bringin' the crazy
extra hard today, huh?

00:25.729 --> 00:26.951
Take a deep breath.

00:29.994 --> 00:32.552
You're the most amazing mom
I've ever seen.

00:32.613 --> 00:34.813
One tiny mistake can't ruin
something that good.

00:35.912 --> 00:37.927
That's the sweetest thing
you've ever said to me.

00:38.497 --> 00:39.371
It is?

00:39.666 --> 00:41.638
This is gonna come back
to you in a good way.

00:42.392 --> 00:45.210
What kind of a good way?
In the boudoir, right?

00:45.563 --> 00:46.466
Up high!

00:46.634 --> 00:49.470
We're getting a little old to be making
such a big deal out of having sex.

00:50.241 --> 00:51.256
Yeah, you're right.

00:52.474 --> 00:55.222
- I'm just playin', man!
- Thank goodness.

00:55.299 --> 00:57.342
When you said that,
I died a little inside.

00:57.624 --> 00:59.117
Give it up for me gettin' some!

01:00.062 --> 01:00.696
Upstairs!

01:01.329 --> 01:02.287
Downstairs!

01:04.027 --> 01:07.176
- I don't really like... downstairs.
- Really? Well, I wanted to try it.

01:08.345 --> 01:09.621
You're ready to do this?

01:10.615 --> 01:12.415
<i>As attending physicians, it was important</i>

01:12.425 --> 01:14.285
<i>that Turk and I took an interest
in the interns.</i>

01:15.123 --> 01:19.766
All right! You're space invaders!
Try and stay together, for goodness sake.

01:20.040 --> 01:21.442
Game on!

01:28.577 --> 01:29.411
Eat it!

01:33.751 --> 01:35.819
All right, Boon!
You're the mother ship.

01:36.174 --> 01:39.978
Josephine, use your annoying voice
to make the mother ship sound.

01:40.310 --> 01:40.936
Go!

01:48.680 --> 01:50.055
Somebody get him some ice!

01:52.722 --> 01:54.345
Does anyone know why we did that?

01:54.859 --> 01:56.504
Because you're so mean and stupid?

01:57.051 --> 01:59.976
No, we did it to teach you an
important lesson about medicine,

02:00.240 --> 02:03.182
which we'll reveal to you once
you've changed into dry scrubs.

02:05.385 --> 02:06.863
- What's the lesson?
- I don't know. We need to come up

02:06.873 --> 02:10.125
with something quick, though, because Boon
has a concussion and his father's a lawyer.

02:10.164 --> 02:11.554
What could we have been teaching them?

02:11.578 --> 02:14.249
All right, listen up.
I'll tell you one thing, people.

02:14.311 --> 02:17.265
You've got to be ready for anything
this hospital trows at you.

02:18.009 --> 02:19.920
- That's perfect.
- I'll go tell the interns.

02:19.966 --> 02:21.772
Wait, wait! Let me write it down
so you don't forget it.

02:21.813 --> 02:22.850
That's a good idea.

02:27.146 --> 02:27.794
Continue.

02:28.456 --> 02:32.903
I've got an overweight patient back there,
who has already had his stomach stapled,

02:32.920 --> 02:37.032
And is now taking diet medication
that gives you painful diarrhea,

02:37.079 --> 02:39.590
whenever you eat more than 15
grams of fat at one sitting.

02:39.658 --> 02:42.929
Anyone want to guess what he's in the
hospital for? I'll give you a hint.

02:43.565 --> 02:46.873
It is very painful, and it rhymes
with schmiorrhea.

02:46.912 --> 02:49.273
You know what, here's an idea.
Patient should just...

02:49.347 --> 02:51.348
pay me to take food right
out of their hands,

02:51.421 --> 02:53.357
before they even have a chance
to cram it down those

02:53.367 --> 02:55.603
disgusting donut mashers they call mouths.

02:55.693 --> 02:57.449
- I mean, honestly...
- God,

02:57.459 --> 02:59.396
Perry, how many times do I have to say it?

02:59.858 --> 03:01.837
We're tired of your speeches.

03:02.586 --> 03:06.531
If you can't stop, I'll have to hire an
orchestra to play that awards show music,

03:06.607 --> 03:09.979
they use to hustle long-winded
hollywood fruitcakes off the stage.

03:10.174 --> 03:12.608
I'm just sick and tired of...

03:17.781 --> 03:19.409
Do you think I should try my new

03:19.419 --> 03:21.934
"I'll take that food right out
of your hands" diet on him?

03:22.405 --> 03:24.826
- Does it matter what I say?
- Does it ever?

03:25.577 --> 03:26.472
No!

03:27.266 --> 03:29.867
<i>Some burns are so bad,
they still get our attention...</i>

03:31.111 --> 03:33.135
Emery, my name is Dr. Dorian.

03:33.508 --> 03:35.503
We're gonna take good care of you, ok?
I promise.

03:37.070 --> 03:38.620
<i>Speaking of getting badly burned...</i>

03:38.860 --> 03:41.479
I'll tell you why I threw water
balloons at you all. All right?

03:42.009 --> 03:44.508
I threw water balloons at
you guys because...

03:45.871 --> 03:48.437
<i>Suck it, bitch!</i>

03:49.801 --> 03:53.922
- I'm so calling my dad.
- You're in trouble now, Mr. Man.

03:55.527 --> 03:57.065
I'm gonna kill J.D.!

